  "text": "In addition to these updates, we have to perform updates that change the value of the action. To this end we implemented a heat-bath algorithm that is applied to the subset of three of the 2N components of z x . The heatbath used here is identical to the one used in the simulation of the O(3)-Heisenberg model on the lattice or for the update of SU (2) subgroups in the simulation of pure SU(N) lattice gauge models [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . We run through all N components of z x taking the real and the complex part of the component as first two components for the heat-bath. The third component is randomly chosen among the real or complex parts of the remaining N − 1 components of z x . Note that the CPU-time required by the microcanonical overrelaxation update is about one order of magnitude less than that for the heat-bath update.",
